criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  There are clinical manifestations of changes in muscle tension of the elbow flexor
             group;

          -  Subject's diagnosis is clear;

          -  The degree of joint mobility meets the method of muscle tension assessment.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Has serious diseases such as heart, lung, liver, kidney, etc., cardiac function grade
             is greater than Grade I (NYHA), has symptoms and signs or examination results such as
             respiratory failure;

          -  History of muscle disorders;

          -  Recent (within 6 months) history of external injury, fracture or surgery of the limb;

          -  Are using drugs that affect muscle tone;

          -  Severe osteoporosis;

          -  Acute phase of inflammation

          -  Acute limb thrombosis of the subject;

          -  Pregnancy.
